{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"03d9861b-ab05-4a3a-ba21-3d0531506f29","content":"Use the `--filter` option:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter FullyQualifiedName~ReportExporterTests\n```\n\nOr equivalently:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"ClassName=ReportExporterTests\"\n```\n\nThe `~` operator does a \"contains\" match, while `=` does an exact match on the class name. Both will run only tests in `ReportExporterTests`, skipping `ReportGeneratorTests`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b414fa6a-1af5-44e1-9348-116a612780bb","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user wants to know how to run only the `ReportExporterTests` class using `dotnet test`. This is a straightforward question about the `dotnet test` CLI filter syntax.","outputTokens":170,"requestId":"340A:3A1698:AB61ED:C92B59:69F40192"},"id":"f1c5e12d-97e6-4515-8490-442a90614fac","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:27:53.001Z","parentId":"d81db8b3-3840-476a-8632-a734fd11512e"}
